(RECOVERY ACTIONS) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Reseat the roll, reposition the media guide, and rerun calibration if the stock is visibly) Tj
0 -14 Td
(off center.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- If software settings are wrong, correct label width, height, and top-of-form values, then) Tj
0 -14 Td
(print a fresh ten-label batch.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- If drift persists after cleaning and settings validation, replace the platen roller and) Tj
0 -14 Td
(retest before escalating.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- If a print-head latch is not closing evenly, remove the printer from service and swap in the) Tj
0 -14 Td
(spare lane device.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(ESCALATION CRITERIA) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Escalate after two failed recalibration attempts on the same stock.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Escalate immediately if the print head cannot latch evenly or if labels wrinkle under the) Tj
0 -14 Td
(print head.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Attach one successful sample label and one failed sample label to the service ticket if the) Tj
0 -14 Td
(issue is intermittent.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(FIELD NOTES) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(A useful question for later RAG testing is whether the guide tells the operator to compare) Tj
0 -14 Td
(workstation settings with a known-good lane before replacing parts. It does, and that detail) Tj
0 -14 Td
(matters because many alignment issues are profile-related rather than hardware-related.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(Another realistic variation is drift that appears only after warm-up. That hints at mechanical) Tj
0 -14 Td
(friction or roller condition instead of a simple gap-sensor position problem.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
ET
endstream
